org.matsim.core.utils.io

Class OsmNetworkReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.matsim.core.utils.io.OsmNetworkReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MatsimSomeReader

    public class OsmNetworkReader
extends Object
implements MatsimSomeReader
    Reads in an OSM-File, exported from OpenStreetMap, and extracts information about roads to generate a MATSim-Network. OSM-Files can be obtained:
    • by exporting the data directly from OpenStreetMap. This works only for smaller regions.
    • by downloading the requested data from OpenStreetMap.
    • by extracting the corresponding data from Planet.osm. Planet.osm contains the complete data from OpenStreetMap and is huge! Thus, you must extract a subset of data to be able to process it. For some countries, there are Extracts available containing only the data of a single country.
    OpenStreetMap only contains limited information regarding traffic flow in the streets. The most valuable attribute of OSM data is a categorization of "ways". This reader allows to set defaults how those categories should be interpreted to create a network with suitable attributes for traffic simulation. For the most common highway-types, some basic defaults can be loaded automatically (see code), but they can be overwritten if desired. If the optional attributes lanes and oneway are set in the osm data, they overwrite the default values. Using hierarchy layers, multiple overlapping areas can be specified, each with a different denseness, e.g. one only containing motorways, a second one containing every link down to footways.
    Author:
    mrieser, aneumann

        Sets defaults for converting OSM highway paths into MATSim links, assuming it is no oneway road.
        Parameters:
        hierarchy - The hierarchy layer the highway appears.
        highwayType - The type of highway these defaults are for.
        lanesPerDirection - number of lanes on that road type in each direction
        freespeed - the free speed vehicles can drive on that road type [meters/second]
        freespeedFactor - the factor the freespeed is scaled
        laneCapacity_vehPerHour - the capacity per lane [veh/h]
        See Also:
        http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Map_Features#Highway

      • setKeepPaths

        public void setKeepPaths(boolean keepPaths)
        Sets whether the detailed geometry of the roads should be retained in the conversion or not. Keeping the detailed paths results in a much higher number of nodes and links in the resulting MATSim network. Not keeping the detailed paths removes all nodes where only one road passes through, thus only real intersections or branchings are kept as nodes. This reduces the number of nodes and links in the network, but can in some rare cases generate extremely long links (e.g. for motorways with only a few ramps every few kilometers). Defaults to false.
        Parameters:
        keepPaths - true to keep all details of the OSM roads

      • setScaleMaxSpeed

        public void setScaleMaxSpeed(boolean scaleMaxSpeed)
        In case the speed limit allowed does not represent the speed a vehicle can actually realize, e.g. by constrains of traffic lights not explicitly modeled, a kind of "average simulated speed" can be used. Defaults to false.
        Parameters:
        scaleMaxSpeed - true to scale the speed limit down by the value specified by the defaults.

      • setHierarchyLayer

        public void setHierarchyLayer(double coordNWNorthing,

                              double coordSENorthing,
                              double coordSEEasting,
                              int hierarchy)
        Defines a new hierarchy layer by specifying a rectangle and the hierarchy level to which highways will be converted.
        Parameters:
        coordNWNorthing - The latitude of the north western corner of the rectangle.
        coordNWEasting - The longitude of the north western corner of the rectangle.
        coordSENorthing - The latitude of the south eastern corner of the rectangle.
        coordSEEasting - The longitude of the south eastern corner of the rectangle.
        hierarchy - Layer specifying the hierarchy of the layers starting with 1 as the top layer.

      • setMemoryOptimization

        public void setMemoryOptimization(boolean memoryEnabled)
        By default, this converter caches a lot of data internally to speed up the network generation. This can lead to OutOfMemoryExceptions when converting huge osm files. By enabling this memory optimization, the converter tries to reduce its memory usage, but will run slower.
        Parameters:
        memoryEnabled -
